{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"68d78400-f9d1-4547-9cd1-c08099cae6f9","content":"This is a **TUnit** project (MTP-native), so it uses `--treenode-filter` syntax. The treenode path is `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test`.\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nThis matches any assembly, any namespace, the `SmsNotificationTests` class, and all tests within it. The `--` separates `dotnet test` args from the MTP runner args.\n\nAlternatively, since TUnit projects are `Exe`-based, you can use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2c5bc87e-4666-4c94-af71-0c725b4b9551","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For TUnit with MTP, the filter syntax uses `--treenode-filter` rather than `--filter`.\n\nThe TUnit treenode filter to match a class is:\n\n```\n/**/*SmsNotificationTests*\n```\n\nOr more precisely:\n\n```\n/**/*SmsNotificationTests/**\n```\n\nThe command would be:\n\n```\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*SmsNotificationTests*\"\n```\n\nWait, but the user asked about `dotnet test`. Let me think about how TUnit works.\n\n\nWith TUnit 0.6.x as an MTP-native runner, I can use `dotnet run` with the `--treenode-filter` flag directly, or try `dotnet test` with a filter, though the exact syntax depends on the SDK version and how the MTP integration is set up. I'm realizing that with `dotnet test` and TUnit's MTP-based runner, the filtering approach depends on the .NET SDK version—in .NET 9+, `--filter` with MSTest-like expressions should work, but TUnit natively uses treenode filters which have a different path structure. I should probably use the run-tests skill to handle the TUnit-specific syntax correctly since this can be tricky. The project's `OutputType=Exe` confirms it's an MTP project, so the treenode filter approach is the right way to go. The path structure `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test` means `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*` will match the test class and all tests within it.","outputTokens":1244,"requestId":"7C19:97105:12F8293:15958AF:69F94860"},"id":"aed4c225-0492-4378-a582-5162be3ce72b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:31:38.056Z","parentId":"f9dd6b99-b223-4bbc-a01c-564ca834e923"}
